      "amount": "1/4 teaspoon",
      "notes": "or more to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "olive oil",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons",
      "notes": "for cooking"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the lamb to the skillet and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, cumin, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper to the skillet and cook until the onion is translucent.",
    "Stir in the cooked brown rice and cook for 2 minutes.",
    "In a large bowl, combine the lamb and rice mixture and mix well.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a serving platter and shape into a maqluba.",
    "Cover the platter with aluminum foil and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.",
    "To serve, slice the maqluba into wedges and serve hot."
  ],
